  "text": "REGD. NO. D. L.-33004/99 The Gazette of India EXTRAORDINARY PART II—Section 3—Sub-section (ii) PUBLISHED BY AUTHORITY No. 52] NEW DELHI, TUESDAY, JANUARY 25, 2000/MAGHA 5,1921 MINISTRY OF ENVIRONMENT AND FORESTS ORDER New Delhi, the 25th January. 2000 S.O. 68(E).—In exercise of the powers conferred by Sub-section (3) of Section 3 of the Environment (Protection) Act. 1986 (29 of 1986), the Central Government hereby makes the following amendment in the notification of the Government of India in the Ministry of Environment and Forests, number S.O. 93(E) dated the 29th January, 1998, namely :— In the said notification, in paragraph 1. for the words \"for a period of two years\", the words \"for a period of four years\" shall be substituted. [F. No. Q-18011/14/90-CPA(Vol. XI)] VIJAI SHARMA. Jt. Secy. Note : The principal notification was published in the Gazette of India vide number S.O 93(E) dated 29th January. 1998 Printed by the Manager, Govt of India Press, Ring Road, Mayapuri,New Delhi-110064 and Published by the Controller of Publications, Delhi-110054 232 GI/ 2000 -- 1 of 2 -- -- 2 of 2 --",
